---
title: How a Wi-Fi Talos worker joins the routed cluster
config:
  layout: elk
---
flowchart LR
  accTitle: Routed Wi-Fi Talos worker architecture
  accDescr: Omni on the management NUC asks the provider on the Wi-Fi CachyOS host to create a Talos virtual machine. Firewalla routes the virtual-machine subnet to the host, while Cilium routes a unique pod subnet to each Talos node.

  subgraph MANAGEMENT["MANAGEMENT"]
    direction TB
    GIT["`Git desired state
    machine class and cluster template`"]
    OMNI["`Omni on NUC
    machine lifecycle and Talos config`"]
    GIT desired@--> OMNI
  end

  subgraph UNDERLAY["ROUTED WI-FI UNDERLAY"]
    direction LR
    CORE["`Wired Talos core
    control plane and GPU worker
    HomeLab node addresses`"]
    FW["`Firewalla
    route VM subnet to Dell
    route pod subnets to owners`"]
    DELL["`CachyOS Dell on Wi-Fi
    libvirt and Omni provider
    routes without internal NAT`"]
    VM["`Talos worker VM
    routed node address
    no workload storage ownership`"]
    CORE coreToFw@<--> FW
    FW fwToDell@<--> DELL
    DELL dellToVm@<--> VM
  end

  subgraph PODS["KUBERNETES DATA PLANE"]
    direction TB
    EXISTING["`Existing Cilium pod CIDRs
    one non-overlapping range per node`"]
    DELL_PODS["`Dell Cilium pod CIDR
    assigned when worker joins`"]
    EXISTING podRoute@<--> DELL_PODS
  end

  OMNI request@--> DELL
  CORE ownsExisting@--> EXISTING
  VM ownsDell@--> DELL_PODS

  classDef action fill:#fde8e8,stroke:#dc8c8c,color:#17212b
  classDef desired fill:#e1f3e8,stroke:#7bc397,color:#17212b
  classDef controller fill:#dff4f6,stroke:#70bcc4,color:#17212b
  classDef external fill:#fff3df,stroke:#d8ad55,color:#17212b
  class GIT desired
  class OMNI,DELL,VM controller
  class FW external
  class CORE,EXISTING,DELL_PODS action

  desired@{ animation: slow }
  request@{ animation: fast }
  coreToFw@{ animation: fast }
  fwToDell@{ animation: fast }
  dellToVm@{ animation: fast }
  ownsExisting@{ animation: slow }
  ownsDell@{ animation: slow }
  podRoute@{ animation: fast }
